mmit_sha":"f972c93fc7d596dd9aa91d51009f580c03769f86","position":"1784435046496941001-12acc0c0-60f6-4e8e-8425-3454579de182"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"e5259f5e15d3ac0c558f28cf29fb89cee0340e9d689bbef96c85545745ef4207","event_uuid":"6e54412d-4fc0-40d4-a313-1caa087e4357","position":{"commit_sha":"ccaff94d17098e791a63d02406b49d11a8c6e925","position":"1784436159357223001-6e54412d-4fc0-40d4-a313-1caa087e4357"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"09b38365d746c3aff9f3303e5585587dd6a89894d6480b29d3e16b1e2f6ac437","event_uuid":"ca27445b-ce7e-4806-ad35-ff1f4253c25f","position":{"commit_sha":"28adef6760b7f3109f61169369b87aaac1204a40","position":"1784437174909442001-ca27445b-ce7e-4806-ad35-ff1f4253c25f"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"76df276c5c5ffa59f0f437403e6b785de8dab96c1f5958464fb2c8101e34c612","event_uuid":"516f85ea-611b-4734-a749-206b45f6e0b6","position":{"commit_sha":"019cb2b5b1950d073b470eaccdbdb57bb25ecc20","position":"1784437177643784001-516f85ea-611b-4734-a749-206b45f6e0b6"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":null,"claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":null,"comments":[],"created_at":1784431504420231001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Context\nPass 3 of the GitHub Code Quality remediation. Of 230 'present' findings, 201 are dismissed as churn/intentional. This ticket remediates the reliability/maintainability subset in one change. Every symbol below was grep-verified before removal; symbols found to be USED were deliberately KEPT (listed under 'Retained').\n\n## Scope\n### Tier 1\n- AI-1 (env-inheritance bug) in TWO sibling reconciler reads: reconcile_helpers.py:_read_local_tickets AND run_differs.py:_read_local_ticket_full. Both had `_env = dict(_os.environ, REBAR_SYNC_PULL=\"off\") if no_sync else None`, so when no_sync=False (`_env=None`) the subprocess inherits the parent env — a caller's ambient REBAR_SYNC_PULL=off then silently suppresses the live sync pull. Fix both: build an explicit env, set REBAR_SYNC_PULL=off only when no_sync=True, and strip the key on the live path. A grep confirms no other site carries this pattern. Two regression tests added (one per function).\n- Remove the DEAD-COPY _HAVE_ASTGREP capability flag from tests/unit/grounding/test_conformance.py and tests/unit/grounding/test_coverage_reconstruction.py: in BOTH files it is defined but never referenced in any skipif (the ast-grep missing-tool test in test_conformance.py monkeypatches _ASTGREP_CANDIDATES instead). NOTE: test_engine_b.py legitimately USES _HAVE_ASTGREP (skipif at lines 231 and 360) and is deliberately untouched.\n- test_validation_depth.py (AI-3b): add a non-review (category: transform) test proving input-contract validation is category-agnostic.\n- runners.py + code_review/batch_runner.py (#450): align the BatchRunner.run signature. ProductionBatchRunner already takes agent_runner optional (agent_runner=None, tested via a 1-arg call); to keep the override contract mypy-consistent, make agent_runner optional in the base BatchRunner, DefaultBatchRunner, and CodeReviewBatchRunner too.\n### Tier 2 — remove these EXACT verified-dead symbols\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/acli_graph.py: _RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK (dead duplicate of outbound_links._RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK).\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile_check.py: _PRIORITY_JIRA_TO_LOCAL, _TYPE_JIRA_TO_LOCAL (unused reverse maps; forward maps kept, still used).\n- src/rebar/_engine_support/reads.py: _SCRIPTS_DIR (+ its now-orphaned _engine_dir import).\n- src/rebar/grounding/resolve.py: _REFUTE_ELIGIBLE_KINDS.\n- tests/scripts/graph/_helpers.py: _UUID_A, _UUID_B, _UUID_C, _UUID_D (unused fixture constants).\n- tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_links.py: _LINK_UUID3, _ALIAS_LINK_UUID, _ALIAS_SOURCE_UUID.\n- tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_tag_delta.py: _UUID_C only.\n- tests/scripts/test_ticket_unblock.py: _UUID_A, _UUID_B, _UUID_C.\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/conflict/test_read_latest_status_reducer.py: _ENGINE_DIR.\n- tests/unit/test_overlap_judge.py: dead nested def _boom (never called; _BoomRunner.run is live).\n\n### Retained (verified USED — NOT removed)\n- test_engine_b.py _HAVE_ASTGREP (used in skipif at lines 231, 360).\n- test_reducer_links.py _ALIAS_TARGET_UUID (used at lines ~499/548/568-569).\n- test_reducer_tag_delta.py _UUID_A, _UUID_B (used throughout the module).\n- _SCAN_MAX_FILES (enforced in pai_tools.search_files:126-129) and _deprecations._KINDS (used in test_deprecation_registry.py) — CodeQL 'unused in-module' false positives; recorded as such.\n- engine_b _OPENGREP/_METRIC/_GITLEAKS_CANDIDATES and the two module-cache stores (_LinkDirModule/_AdfModule_Inbound) — cross-module-wired / real caches with 'global'.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] AI-1 fixed in BOTH reconcile_helpers.py and run_differs.py; two regression tests assert the live path strips an ambient REBAR_SYNC_PULL=off and no_sync=True still sets it off (verified by `pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/orchestrate/test_orchestrator_wiring.py -k sync_pull` passing).\n- [ ] _HAVE_ASTGREP removed from test_conformance.py and test_coverage_reconstruction.py, verified by `git grep -n _HAVE_ASTGREP tests/unit/grounding/test_conformance.py tests/unit/grounding/test_coverage_reconstruction.py` returning no matches (test_engine_b.py retains its used copy).\n- [ ] AI-3b non-review category test added and passing (verified by `pytest tests/unit/workflow/test_validation_depth.py -k non_review` passing).\n- [ ] Exactly the enumerated Tier-2 symbols removed, verified by `ruff check --select F821` clean on the changed files (no dangling references) plus `git grep -w <symbol>` returning only the removed definition line; retained symbols untouched, confirmed by inspecting `git diff`.\n- [ ] BatchRunner.run signatures aligned, verified by `mypy src/rebar` reporting success (override-compatibility clean).\n- [ ] `make lint` + `mypy src/rebar` clean; the touched test modules pass in-session.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] the single Gerrit change lands only after LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1 (external gates, verified out-of-session).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/acli_graph.py","reason":"Tier-2: remove verified-dead symbol"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile_check.py","reason":"Tier-2: remove verified-dead symbol"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile_helpers.py","reason":"AI-1: strip ambient REBAR_SYNC_PULL on live path"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/run_differs.py","reason":"AI-1: strip ambient REBAR_SYNC_PULL on live path"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine_support/reads.py","reason":"Tier-2: remove verified-dead symbol"},{"path":"src/rebar/grounding/resolve.py","reason":"Tier-2: remove verified-dead symbol"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/code_review/batch_runner.py","reason":"#450: align run() signature"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/workflow/runners.py","reason":"#450: align run() signature"},{"path":"tests/scripts/graph/_helpers.py","reason":"Tier-2: remove verified-dead symbol"},{"path":"tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_links.py","reason":"Tier-2: remove verified-dead symbol"},{"path":"tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_tag_delta.py","reason":"Tier-2: remove verified-dead symbol"},{"path":"tests/scripts/test_ticket_unblock.py","reason":"Tier-2: remove verified-dead symbol"},{"path":"tests/unit/grounding/test_conformance.py","reason":"remove dead-copy _HAVE_ASTGREP"},{"path":"tests/unit/grounding/test_coverage_reconstruction.py","reason":"remove dead-copy _HAVE_ASTGREP"},{"path":"tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/conflict/test_read_latest_status_reducer.py","reason":"Tier-2: remove verified-dead symbol"},{"path":"tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/orchestrate/test_orchestrator_wiring.py","reason":"AI-1 regression tests (both sibling reads)"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_overlap_judge.py","reason":"Tier-2: remove verified-dead symbol"},{"path":"tests/unit/workflow/test_validation_depth.py","reason":"AI-3b non-review category coverage"}],"keyring":[],"managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":3,"reverts":[],"status":"open","tags":["code-quality","codeql","cleanup"],"ticket_id":"62a3-a49d-04a0-4f18","ticket_type":"task","title":"Remediate Tier-1/2 GitHub Code Quality 'present' findings (Pass 3)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["74e72d3a-f2d6-4572-815b-3aee0d817dda","c4526dd1-8dd7-4927-a5c9-10001c11cee7","edc93179-2ba7-4c74-8505-088ce6c2928b","eeb5df7c-0908-47c8-ab51-1e28d49404a6","b0a31b15-7116-4455-9144-fc1e81adee90","14fe7fdf-6071-4bb5-a0b5-8b8832860989","12acc0c0-60f6-4e8e-8425-3454579de182","6e54412d-4fc0-40d4-a313-1caa087e4357","ca27445b-ce7e-4806-ad35-ff1f4253c25f","516f85ea-611b-4734-a749-206b45f6e0b6"]},"env_id":"ade0